Ning et al. found that the incorporation of PEAI ligand would help to form quasi-2D perovskite on top of the Sn-based perovskite film. Further, they incorporated pseudo-halogen ammonium thiocyanate (NH4SCN) in Sn-based perovskite to manipulate the crystal growth process. Characterization results indicated that a 2D-quasi-2D-3D hierarchy structure perovskite (HSP) structure was formed. XRD pattern showed that with the inclusion of 5% NH4SCN, two additional peaks at angles of 5.5∘\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
